author: gstein
msg: Upgrade our SWIG stuff to use SWIG 1.3.10.
* svn_types.i: replace the OUT_PARAM preprocessor macro with the
OUTPARAM typemap. this is simpler, as the type is automatically
parameterized and we don't need the OUT_PARAM_S variety.
(MAKE_TYPE, MAKE_PLAIN_TYPE): eliminated. SWIG is better about
tracking the types that it uses, so we don't have to force any
into the file. (and if we should, there is a new %types directive
('const char *' memberin typemap): SWIG was using the 'char *'
typemap for member setters, but that failed for const
members. define a new one that works, and will match first.
(exception typemaps): remove the except typemap (deprecated) and
just use an 'out' typemap to handle the svn_error_t return value.
(svn_revnum_t * typemap): apply the 'long *OUTPUT' typemap to this
rather than copying individual typemaps (which doesn't seem to
work anyways).
* svn_ra.i: use new OUTPARAM typemap for the svn_ra_plugin_t type.
* svn_string.i: rename typemap vars to 1.3.10 names.
* util.i: temporarily ignore svn_io_open_unique_file until we fix up
the stringbuf handling, or change the function signature.
(apr_size_t * typemap): apply the INOUT typemap rather than copying
(const char ** typemap): apply instead of copy
* svn_fs.i: replace some OUT_PARAM() macro usage with the new OUTPARAM
typemap defined in svn_types.i.
(int * typemap): apply the OUTPUT typemap rather than copying
(svn_fs_parse_id typemap): use 1.3.10's new multi-var typemaps to
properly handle the ptr/len pair here.
(const char ** typemap): apply OUTPUT typemap instead of copying
(apr_hash_t ** typemap): apply PROPHASH typemap instead of copying
<various>: rename typemap vars to 1.3.10 names.
eliminate the MAKE_* macro usage.
* svn_repos.i: eliminate the MAKE_* macro usage.
(svn_repos_t **): use the OUTPARAM typemap instead of the macro
* svn_delta.i: use new OUTPARAM typemap for various types.
<various>: rename typemap vars to 1.3.10 names.
* apr.i (apr_off_t * typemap): apply the 'long * OUTPUT' typemap
rather than copying it.
<various>: rename typemap vars to 1.3.10 names.
* svn_client.i: rename typemap vars to 1.3.10 names.
* swigutil.h (MAKE_*): toss the MAKE_* macros; the new SWIG handles
this stuff better.
(SWIG_NewPointerObj): add a param
* swigutil.c (convert_to_swigtype): SWIG_NewPointerObj grew a new
variable ('owner'). it should be set to zero.
* README: fix a minor nit

author: sussman
msg: Command-line client: rewrite the subcommand alias system to be
similar to the options system.
* main.c (svn_cl__cmd_desc_t): remove 'is_alias' boolean field.  add
new field -- an array of alias names.
(SVN_CL__MAX_ALIASES): new #define.
(svn_cl__cmd_table):  remove is_alias field, add alias name arrays
to each subcommand structure.
(print_command_info): loop over aliases differently.
(svn_cl__print_generic_help): remove extra alias check.
(get_cmd_table_entry):  removed, folded into svn_cl__get_canonical_command.
(svn_cl__get_canonical_command):  rewritten.
